detaileddescription.para: Creates an external event for the given model with the given name and the specified tracemode.

parameterdescription.para: boolean : Flag for showing this external event in tracemessages

detaileddescription.para: Implement this method to express the semantics of this external event. External events are supposed to act on the model or experiment in general. They are not related to a special Entity (unlike method eventRoutine(Entity who) of class Event). Override this method to implement this Externalevent's behaviour.
Schedules this external event to make the desired changes to the experiment or model at the current point of time plus the given span of time

parameterdescription.para: TimeSpan : The offset to the current simulation time at which this external event is to be scheduled

detaileddescription.para: Schedules this external event to make the desired changes to the experiment or model. The time instant for which the event is scheduled is determined by a sample from the distribution provided to the method. The sample is interpreted as offset from the the present time in the reference time unit.

parameterdescription.para: NumericalDist<?> : Numerical distribution to sample the offset to the current simulation time from

detaileddescription.para: Schedules this external event to make the desired changes to the experiment or model at the specified point in simulation time.

parameterdescription.para: TimeInstant : The point in simulation time this external event is scheduled to happen.

xrefdescription.para: Replaced by schedule(TimeSpan dt).Schedules this external Event to make the desired changes to the experiment or model at the specified point in simulation time. The point of time is given as an offset to the current simulation time as displayed by the simclock.

parameterdescription.para: SimTime : The offset to the current simulation time this event is to happen

detaileddescription.para: Schedules this external event to act on the experiment or model state directly after the given Schedulable is already set to be activated. Note that this external event's point of simulation time will be set to be the same as the Schedulable's time. Thus this external event will occur directly after the given Schedulable but the simulation clock will not change. Make sure that the Schedulable given as parameter is actually scheduled.

parameterdescription.para: Schedulable : The Schedulable this external event should be scheduled after

detaileddescription.para: Schedules this external event to act on the experiment or model state directly before the given Schedulable is already set to be activated. Note that this external event's point of simulation time will be set to be the same as the Schedulable's time. Thus this external event will occur directly before the given Schedulable but the simulation clock will not change. Make sure that the Schedulable given as parameter is actually scheduled.

parameterdescription.para: Schedulable : The Schedulable this external event should be scheduled before

detaileddescription.para: Creates and returns a copy of this event. Note that subclasses have to implement the interface java.lang.Cloneable to actually use this method as otherwise, a CloneNotSupportedException will be thrown.

simplesect.para: ExternalEvent : A copy of this event.

detaileddescription.para: Provides the class for user defined events to change the model's state at a distinct point in simulation time.

For events specifically changing the state of up to three entities, refer to Event, EventOf2Entities and EventOf3Entities. Events not associated to a specific entity are called external events as they are are typically used for external influences, e.g. arrivals from outside or incidents.
Derive from this class to design special external events for a model. To use external events, always create a new object of this class.
